1 A MEMORIAL
2 DECLARING JANUARY 29, 2026 "NEW MEXICO TRIO PROGRAMS DAY" IN
3 THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES.
4
5 WHEREAS, TRIO is a series of programs funded by the
6 United States department of education that helps
7 first-generation, low-income students access higher
8 education; and
9 WHEREAS, TRIO derives its name from the initiative's
10 original three programs: upward bound, created in 1964;
11 educational talent search, created in 1965; and special
12 services for disadvantaged students, created in 1968 and now
13 known as student support services; and
14 WHEREAS, since 1986, congress has recognized a "National
15 TRIO Day" in recognition of the achievements of the TRIO
16 programs and the more than ten million students from low-
income and working families that have benefited from the
17
services of TRIO pre-college and college programs; and
18
WHEREAS, 2026 is the sixty-second anniversary of the
19
creation of TRIO programs, and New Mexico was one of the
20
first states to implement these programs; and
21
WHEREAS, all TRIO programs are vested in the notion that
22
committed students deserve an opportunity to obtain higher
23
education without regard to race, gender, national origin,
24
disability status, family economic resources or family
25 HM 14
Page 1

1 educational background; and
2 WHEREAS, in addition to the original three programs,
3 TRIO programs now include talent search, upward bound
4 math/science, veterans upward bound, educational opportunity
5 centers and the Robert E. McNair post-baccalaureate
6 achievement program; and
7 WHEREAS, there are thirty-eight TRIO programs in New
8 Mexico that attract more than twelve million five hundred
9 thousand dollars ($12,500,000) in annual federal funding and
10 serve nearly ten thousand students; and
11 WHEREAS, these successful federal programs help first-
12 generation, low-income students prepare for and gain
13 admission to college and obtain college degrees and should be
14 expanded in order to serve more students;
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF
16 REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO that the New
Mexico TRIO programs be recognized for the important role
17
they play in encouraging and assisting students seeking
18
higher education by declaring January 29, 2026 as "New Mexico
19
TRIO Programs Day" in the house of representatives; and
20
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this memorial be
21
transmitted to Eilleen Garcia, president-elect of the TRIO New
22
Mexico association.
